      <pubDate>Thu, 07 Sep 2023 16:04:48 +0200</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/docs/guides/markov-chain-theory/introduction/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This guide explores the Markov chain theory of rattling developed in &lt;a href=&#34;http://localhost:1313/references/calvertrandall/&#34;&gt;Calvert–Randall (2024)&lt;/a&gt;. It assumes only basic knowledge of finite Markov chains, like the jump-hold description of continuous-time Markov chains and the major theorems about the existence and uniqueness of stationary distributions.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
